# VibeMarketer — Native Desktop App for Vibe Marketers

A native macOS app that turns HABITAT marketing skills into a beautiful, click-to-run experience — no terminal, no code, just marketing workflows powered by AI.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **new project** that will be scaffolded at `/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/vibemarketer`.

## The Concept

**Problem:** Marketers want to use powerful AI marketing skills (like HABITAT's 15 skill library) but the current delivery is CLI-based — `git clone`, terminal commands, slash commands inside Claude Code. That scares away 90% of the target audience.

**Solution:** A downloadable macOS app that:
- Bundles all 15 HABITAT skills in a visual sidebar
- Turns each skill into a friendly form with inputs, dropdowns, and toggles
- Sends the skill + inputs to Claude API and streams beautiful results
- No terminal ever touches the user

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Marketer] -->|clicks skill| B[VibeMarketer App]
    B -->|reads| C[SKILL.md files]
    B -->|sends prompt + context| D[Claude API]
    D -->|streams response| B
    B -->|renders beautifully| A
```

---

## Technology Choice

| Stack | Why |
|-------|-----|
| **Tauri 2.0** | Native macOS app, ~5MB bundle (vs. 200MB Electron), Rust backend |
| **React + Vite** | Fast frontend, rich component ecosystem |
| **Vanilla CSS** | Full control over the premium design (no Tailwind) |
| **Claude API** | Anthropic's Messages API for skill execution |

> [!NOTE]
> Tauri 2.0 gives us a real `.dmg` installer, system tray, native menus, and auto-updates — all the things that make it feel like a proper app. If Tauri setup proves problematic, we can fallback to Electron.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Skill Parser Engine

The HABITAT skills follow a consistent format:
```yaml
---
name: social-content
version: 1.0.0
description: "Create social media content for..."
---

# Social Content
You are helping a founder...

## Before Starting
Check for context first...
```

We need a parser that:
1. Reads the YAML frontmatter → extracts `name`, `version`, `description`
2. Parses the markdown body → extracts sections, instructions, output format
3. Detects input requirements from "Before Starting" / "Gather" sections
4. Maps skills to UI form fields automatically

#### [NEW] [skillParser.js](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/vibemarketer/src/lib/skillParser.js)
- `parseSkillFile(content)` → returns `{ meta, sections, inputs, outputFormat }`
- `extractInputs(content)` → detects required user inputs from skill text
- `buildPrompt(skill, userInputs)` → assembles the full prompt for Claude

---

### Skill Library (Bundled Skills)

All 15 HABITAT skills will be bundled into the app:

| Phase | Skills |
|-------|--------|
| **Ideation & Validation** | founder-context, idea-validation, vc-research, competitor-research, portfolio-research, customer-segments |
| **Prototyping & Building** | landing-page, prototype-sprint, mvp-scope |
| **Launch & Traction** | social-content, first-users, launch-plan, pitch-deck |
| **Meta & Operations** | sprint-coach, onboarding |

#### [NEW] [skills/](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/vibemarketer/src/skills/)
- Copy all 15 [SKILL.md](file:///Users/canerden/habitat-skills/skills/sprint-coach/SKILL.md) files from [habitat-skills](file:///Users/canerden/habitat-skills/skills/) into the app bundle
- Each skill gets a `config.json` with UI metadata (icon, color, category, form fields)

